Park and colleagues,126 investigated 215 patients with full-thickness supraspinatus tears confirmed by arthroscopy and found the Jobe test to have a sensitivity of 52.6% and specificity of 82.4%. For partial-thickness tears, the same study showed the Jobe test to have a 32.1% sensitivity and 67.8% specificity.126" @duttonDuttonOrthopaedicExamination2020 # Dysfunction - Supraspinatus tear - Supraspinatus tendonitis - Supraspinatus tendinopathy - supraspinatus paratenonitis
